  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Guinea - Floods (Nzerekor&#xE9;)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">On 4 July 2017, heavy rainfall hit the forest region of Guinea in the Prefecture of Nzerekore causing serious property damages.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Respond to the immediate needs for 545 households, with specific interventions in the areas of emergency relief, shelter, water, sanitation and hygiene promotion for a period of three months.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This program provides assistance to 545 households affected by the floods, totalling 3,274 people.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This program supports the government-led floods response through the promotion of hygiene and sanitation, access to potable water, supply of shelter kits and non-food items to the affected population in the 8 urban areas of Nzerekore.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is located in the city of Nzerekore.</narrative>
  </description>
